  "body": "Hi there,\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.9.13-unstable-93ffb85b-20200321`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nresponse with transaction hash string \r\n@see https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Management-APIs#personal_sendtransaction\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nStuck with no response\r\n\r\n#### Description\r\nOn my Geth Node Server after about a week of normal work rcp call of `personal_sendTransaction` stuck with no any response from rpc server. While other rpc calls like `eth_gasPrice`, `eth_syncing`,  `eth_getBalance`, `personal_newAccount`, `personal_listAccounts` etc.  works fine.\r\n\r\nExample of RPC call:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\ncurl -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -X POST --data '{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"method\":\"personal_sendTransaction\",\"params\":[{\"from\": \"0xf8572e_xxx_9345\", \"to\": \"0xf5f81e_xxx_f39\", \"gas\": \"0x5208\", \"gasPrice\": \"0x773594000\", \"value\": \"0xaf3f8dfd7b0000\"}, \"somePassword\"],\"id\":1}' localhost:45868\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhere:\r\ngas = 21000 wei (`0x5208`)\r\ngasPrice = 18000000000 wei (`0x773594000`)\r\n\r\nAny ideas, thanks.\r\n",
